1
00:00:27,527 --> 00:00:30,948
THE HUSBAND

2
00:00:35,202 --> 00:00:36,410
THIS SERIES IS FICTITIOUS

3
00:00:36,411 --> 00:00:39,121
CHILDREN WERE FILMED SAFELY
GEN AI WAS USED IN SELECT SCENES

4
00:01:15,409 --> 00:01:17,369
EPISODE 3

5
00:02:28,774 --> 00:02:30,317
This way! Move!

6
00:02:31,860 --> 00:02:33,069
Hayun.

7
00:02:33,070 --> 00:02:34,738
Oh, my God, Hayun.

8
00:02:37,741 --> 00:02:39,158
Wait, Doctor.

9
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:41,244
Can you wait until Dr. Kang gets here?

10
00:02:41,995 --> 00:02:43,579
We don't have time.

11
00:02:43,580 --> 00:02:45,873
Bone fragments
from her broken cervical vertebrae

12
00:02:45,874 --> 00:02:47,708
are compressing her respiratory center.

13
00:02:47,709 --> 00:02:50,671
If we don't operate right now,
she's going into respiratory arrest.

14
00:02:51,254 --> 00:02:52,672
We'll try our best.

15
00:02:52,673 --> 00:02:54,716
Ms. Ko. I have to ask you
to wait out here.

16
00:03:01,348 --> 00:03:05,559
WOORI TOGETHER MEDICAL CENTER

17
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:07,312
CALLING
HUSBAND

18
00:03:08,939 --> 00:03:11,816
Come on, honey, pick up.

19
00:03:11,817 --> 00:03:13,360
Please. Hayun is…

20
00:03:16,363 --> 00:03:18,365
Why won't he pick up?

21
00:03:20,158 --> 00:03:21,827
Where on earth is he?

22
00:03:24,538 --> 00:03:25,539
Blade.

23
00:03:30,627 --> 00:03:31,753
Bovie, please.

24
00:04:04,744 --> 00:04:05,745
Vitals are dropping.

25
00:04:06,663 --> 00:04:07,831
Give me an amp of epi.

26
00:04:19,843 --> 00:04:21,845
Oh, please…

27
00:04:26,475 --> 00:04:27,559
She's flatlining!

28
00:04:36,359 --> 00:04:38,612
The patient is flatlining.
Keep compressions going.

29
00:04:39,488 --> 00:04:40,697
Get the crash cart in here!

30
00:05:13,647 --> 00:05:16,191
Ms. Ko, we're sorry.

31
00:05:17,150 --> 00:05:18,777
We did our best, but…

32
00:05:55,814 --> 00:05:57,106
Dr. Kang.

33
00:05:57,107 --> 00:05:58,900
RESTRICTED AREA
AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY

34
00:06:15,959 --> 00:06:17,460
Where have you been?

35
00:06:33,518 --> 00:06:36,855
I said, where have you been?

36
00:06:44,738 --> 00:06:46,823
Where have you been?

37
00:06:51,786 --> 00:06:53,538
Answer me!

38
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:57,667
Where the hell have you been?

39
00:06:59,461 --> 00:07:00,462
While…

40
00:07:03,923 --> 00:07:08,011
Where were you while our Hayun was dying?

41
00:07:17,145 --> 00:07:18,605
This is all your fault.

42
00:07:21,566 --> 00:07:23,276
It's all your fault.

43
00:07:29,324 --> 00:07:31,117
This whole thing is your fault.

44
00:07:35,413 --> 00:07:38,083
This is all your fault!

45
00:07:42,796 --> 00:07:47,717
THE HUSBAND

46
00:07:49,803 --> 00:07:52,262
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

47
00:07:52,263 --> 00:07:54,265
How do you know the kidnapper?

48
00:07:55,684 --> 00:07:57,143
I don't know him.

49
00:07:58,103 --> 00:08:00,646
He showed up when I called for a driver.

50
00:08:00,647 --> 00:08:02,691
So you solicited

51
00:08:03,566 --> 00:08:05,402
a complete stranger to murder your wife?

52
00:08:06,069 --> 00:08:07,820
I never solicited anything.

53
00:08:07,821 --> 00:08:11,116
Mr. Kang, where's your accomplice?

54
00:08:13,702 --> 00:08:15,911
I really don't know.
I didn't put him up to it.

55
00:08:15,912 --> 00:08:17,663
Tell us. You know where she is!

56
00:08:17,664 --> 00:08:20,749
I said I don't know!

57
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:22,418
Your accomplice…

58
00:08:22,419 --> 00:08:25,671
He's way more dangerous than you think.

59
00:08:25,672 --> 00:08:27,799
You're going to end up
taking the fall alone.

60
00:08:28,425 --> 00:08:32,929
Just how many times do I have to tell you?

61
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:35,724
You're losing time here!

62
00:08:36,599 --> 00:08:40,478
Do you have any idea
what a waste of time this is?

63
00:08:40,979 --> 00:08:44,273
This guy is a psycho!
My wife is in danger!

64
00:08:44,274 --> 00:08:45,357
Calm down, Mr. Kang.

65
00:08:45,358 --> 00:08:46,484
I'm serious!

66
00:08:47,027 --> 00:08:49,611
There's no time to be screwing around!

67
00:08:49,612 --> 00:08:50,613
Mr. Kang!

68
00:08:57,537 --> 00:08:58,913
Calm now?

69
00:09:01,207 --> 00:09:04,043
Wash your face off.
And freshen up a little.

70
00:09:04,044 --> 00:09:05,586
That one doesn't work.

71
00:09:05,587 --> 00:09:06,755
Use the next one.

72
00:09:08,965 --> 00:09:10,466
What the hell?

73
00:09:10,467 --> 00:09:14,887
Man, it's about time
they fix this place up.

74
00:09:14,888 --> 00:09:16,472
Nothing works in here.

75
00:09:20,518 --> 00:09:22,227
Hey, Captain Kim.

76
00:09:22,228 --> 00:09:24,856
Yeah. It's been too long.

77
00:09:25,356 --> 00:09:27,316
Oh, that? Yeah, it was really helpful.

78
00:09:27,317 --> 00:09:28,443
Take your time, okay?

79
00:09:28,985 --> 00:09:32,405
Right, I was going to come and see you.

80
00:09:34,491 --> 00:09:36,826
Come on, not this again.

81
00:09:38,286 --> 00:09:40,287
What the hell, man?

82
00:09:40,288 --> 00:09:42,247
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

83
00:09:42,248 --> 00:09:44,584
SAFE SEONGJIN, TRUSTED POLICE

84
00:09:45,710 --> 00:09:48,630
I didn't do it,
but everyone thinks I did.

85
00:09:50,215 --> 00:09:52,217
No one believes me.

86
00:09:53,301 --> 00:09:54,594
Who would?

87
00:09:58,848 --> 00:10:00,141
No one believes you.

88
00:10:01,768 --> 00:10:04,020
Why would anyone believe you, Mr. Kang?

89
00:10:08,650 --> 00:10:10,068
Who are you?

90
00:10:14,864 --> 00:10:16,199
I said, who are you?

91
00:10:17,408 --> 00:10:22,539
I'm the only one who knows
you didn't plot your wife's death.

92
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:26,501
What?

93
00:10:34,175 --> 00:10:35,260
Mr. Kang.

94
00:10:39,639 --> 00:10:40,640
Mr. Kang.

95
00:10:41,432 --> 00:10:42,684
Mr. Kang!

96
00:10:45,228 --> 00:10:48,147
- Mr. Kang!
- Oh, yes. I'm right here.

97
00:10:48,148 --> 00:10:49,691
Why didn't you answer any…

98
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:51,568
You going to be a while?

99
00:10:52,068 --> 00:10:53,194
Little bit, yeah.

100
00:10:54,028 --> 00:10:56,530
Power's out, but don't panic.

101
00:10:56,531 --> 00:10:58,115
And make it quick.

102
00:10:58,116 --> 00:10:59,993
Okay, I got it. Sorry.

103
00:11:22,849 --> 00:11:23,850
So who are you?

104
00:11:27,812 --> 00:11:30,315
How do you know
I didn't have my wife kidnapped?

105
00:11:31,858 --> 00:11:35,153
What's important isn't how I know,

106
00:11:35,945 --> 00:11:38,072
but whether your wife is alive
or not right now.

107
00:11:39,991 --> 00:11:41,491
What?

108
00:11:41,492 --> 00:11:44,537
I doubt there's anyone you can trust
besides me right now.

109
00:11:46,748 --> 00:11:48,291
Who the hell are you?

110
00:11:49,709 --> 00:11:50,793
I told you.

111
00:11:51,502 --> 00:11:55,965
I'm the only one who knows
you didn't have your wife kidnapped.

112
00:11:57,508 --> 00:12:00,303
Or rather, I'm the only one
who can help you.

113
00:12:04,515 --> 00:12:05,516
So…

114
00:12:06,559 --> 00:12:09,395
Seyun is alive, right?

115
00:12:10,605 --> 00:12:12,023
Where is she right now?

116
00:12:12,899 --> 00:12:17,862
If you want to find your wife,
come to 543-7, Shinyu-dong by 11 p.m.

117
00:12:19,405 --> 00:12:20,781
What was that?

118
00:12:20,782 --> 00:12:21,783
If you don't,

119
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:24,701
you may never get to see her again.

120
00:12:24,702 --> 00:12:29,206
Look, man.
I'm being held here as a suspect.

121
00:12:29,207 --> 00:12:31,251
How am I supposed to get there by 11 p.m.?

122
00:12:32,210 --> 00:12:33,586
Remember.

123
00:12:34,587 --> 00:12:37,757
It's 543-7, Shinyu-dong.
Get there by 11 p.m.

124
00:12:45,974 --> 00:12:47,350
For God's sake.

125
00:13:08,413 --> 00:13:10,540
Hayun, Mommy's right here.

126
00:13:15,378 --> 00:13:17,338
Yeah, Hayun, Mommy's right…

127
00:13:49,954 --> 00:13:51,496
There's no time.

128
00:13:51,497 --> 00:13:53,291
I'm running out of time.

129
00:13:54,292 --> 00:13:58,671
When the girl in the red hood
gets swallowed by the snow…

130
00:13:59,547 --> 00:14:00,923
It's over.

131
00:14:06,804 --> 00:14:09,849
- Come on, Mom. Hurry!
- Oh, geez.

132
00:14:12,060 --> 00:14:15,145
This way. Over there.
He's on the second floor. Come on.

133
00:14:15,146 --> 00:14:17,482
ALWAYS WITH THE PEOPLE
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

134
00:14:19,067 --> 00:14:20,068
Mom.

135
00:14:21,277 --> 00:14:27,074
Excuse me, we got a call
saying my son was being held here.

136
00:14:27,075 --> 00:14:29,743
- What's your son's name?
- Taeju. Kang Taeju.

137
00:14:29,744 --> 00:14:32,079
Mr. Kang is in interrogation
at the moment.

138
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:33,455
- What?
- What?

139
00:14:33,456 --> 00:14:35,791
But my brother didn't do anything wrong.

140
00:14:35,792 --> 00:14:39,336
How's my brother the suspect
when his wife's been kidnapped?

141
00:14:39,337 --> 00:14:43,256
Look, sir.
My son would never commit a crime.

142
00:14:43,257 --> 00:14:45,467
This has to be a mistake.

143
00:14:45,468 --> 00:14:47,261
It's not a mistake.

144
00:14:53,768 --> 00:14:55,353
Mr. Ko.

145
00:14:56,354 --> 00:14:58,022
I said, it's not a mistake.

146
00:15:05,113 --> 00:15:06,697
I'm a parent too.

147
00:15:08,449 --> 00:15:11,285
I know you must be heartbroken.

148
00:15:12,370 --> 00:15:14,539
But you know what my Taeju is like

149
00:15:15,081 --> 00:15:17,125
just as well as I do.

150
00:15:17,667 --> 00:15:21,461
Yeah, absolutely.
I know what kind of scum he is.

151
00:15:21,462 --> 00:15:26,466
The despicable kind that plotted
to have my daughter killed.

152
00:15:26,467 --> 00:15:27,510
Excuse me?

153
00:15:31,055 --> 00:15:33,808
I know this is hard, but that's just…

154
00:15:35,852 --> 00:15:38,229
I'd never say that to you, Mr. Ko.

155
00:15:38,729 --> 00:15:40,690
Don't even say my name, okay?

156
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:45,652
It's my own damn fault for letting him
into my family in the first place!

157
00:15:45,653 --> 00:15:49,739
How are you so sure
that Taeju really did it?

158
00:15:49,740 --> 00:15:53,702
I saw with my own two eyes in that video,

159
00:15:53,703 --> 00:15:56,079
how he asked the guy
to get rid of my daughter!

160
00:15:56,080 --> 00:15:57,789
There's no way he did that.

161
00:15:57,790 --> 00:16:02,211
What, you think I'm lying to you
when my daughter's life is on the line?

162
00:16:05,423 --> 00:16:07,300
He's telling the truth.

163
00:16:09,468 --> 00:16:11,679
I saw the video with him.

164
00:16:36,454 --> 00:16:37,705
That's pretty.

165
00:17:32,343 --> 00:17:33,427
Did you sleep well?

166
00:17:37,974 --> 00:17:41,352
I came by earlier,
but you were sleeping so soundly.

167
00:17:42,228 --> 00:17:44,730
How's your neck? Let me take a look.

168
00:17:47,775 --> 00:17:50,820
This is going to take a while to heal.

169
00:17:57,451 --> 00:17:58,953
Here. Try putting this on it.

170
00:18:01,622 --> 00:18:03,082
LIQUID PAIN RELIEVER

171
00:18:03,833 --> 00:18:05,375
Come on, take it.

172
00:18:05,376 --> 00:18:07,085
You'll die when the time comes,

173
00:18:07,086 --> 00:18:09,255
so you might as well
spare yourself the pain now.

174
00:18:09,755 --> 00:18:10,965
Oh, well.

175
00:18:19,932 --> 00:18:21,976
This is how much time you have left.

176
00:18:26,939 --> 00:18:30,317
When the sand runs out, you're dead.

177
00:18:33,613 --> 00:18:36,032
You all right?

178
00:18:37,992 --> 00:18:39,577
Geez, okay.

179
00:18:41,912 --> 00:18:45,123
Right. Apparently, the nuns use this
when they pray at the convent.

180
00:18:45,124 --> 00:18:48,085
You should try praying
if you ever get bored.

181
00:18:49,295 --> 00:18:50,712
Who knows?

182
00:18:50,713 --> 00:18:54,258
You might impress God enough
to get you out of here.

183
00:18:54,759 --> 00:18:57,303
Why are you doing this to me?

184
00:19:09,065 --> 00:19:10,066
Use this, okay?

185
00:19:15,905 --> 00:19:18,948
Why are you doing this to me?

186
00:19:18,949 --> 00:19:21,576
What did I do to deserve this?

187
00:19:21,577 --> 00:19:24,288
What the hell do you want from me?

188
00:19:38,260 --> 00:19:42,181
That driver you'd never seen
before has probably gotten away by now.

189
00:19:43,891 --> 00:19:46,268
Until when do you plan on playing dumb?

190
00:19:48,312 --> 00:19:53,442
If you want to find your wife,
come to 543-7, Shinyu-dong by 11 p.m.

191
00:19:58,656 --> 00:19:59,990
Mr. Kang!

192
00:20:01,075 --> 00:20:02,660
We need you to focus here!

193
00:20:08,874 --> 00:20:11,544
We found this in the trunk of your car.

194
00:20:12,378 --> 00:20:14,588
INSIDE THE TRUNK
OF THE SUSPECT'S VEHICLE

195
00:20:15,256 --> 00:20:16,882
Even the blood splatter matches.

196
00:20:17,508 --> 00:20:18,509
Isn't that funny?

197
00:20:19,427 --> 00:20:22,888
I mean, how could this
have made it into your car?

198
00:20:24,432 --> 00:20:26,392
I said, did you bring my billion won?

199
00:20:45,494 --> 00:20:46,619
I have no idea.

200
00:20:46,620 --> 00:20:47,704
"No idea," huh?

201
00:20:47,705 --> 00:20:50,875
You were there
when the photo was taken, weren't you?

202
00:20:52,460 --> 00:20:55,378
Obviously, he left it in my trunk
without me knowing.

203
00:20:55,379 --> 00:20:58,174
It's also obvious
that he sent you that email.

204
00:20:59,884 --> 00:21:01,176
Is that so?

205
00:21:01,177 --> 00:21:04,262
In that case,
where's the memory card for your dashcam?

206
00:21:04,263 --> 00:21:05,681
That'd prove your innocence.

207
00:21:06,807 --> 00:21:09,143
That's… It disappeared.

208
00:21:09,769 --> 00:21:12,729
Yeah. He probably took that too.

209
00:21:12,730 --> 00:21:16,317
Wow, such unfortunate timing, isn't it?

210
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:21,113
People from the hospital
saw you arguing at the banquet.

211
00:21:22,531 --> 00:21:25,451
Don't tell me this is
a marriage problem gone too far.

212
00:21:26,452 --> 00:21:30,080
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

213
00:22:02,738 --> 00:22:07,034
The moment we get the lab results back,
you're going to be detained.

214
00:22:08,619 --> 00:22:09,703
So come on.

215
00:22:10,204 --> 00:22:12,248
It's not too late to come clean.

216
00:22:13,290 --> 00:22:16,919
It's in your best interest
to keep Ms. Ko alive.

217
00:22:17,461 --> 00:22:18,546
Isn't that right?

218
00:22:37,314 --> 00:22:38,315
Do it now.

219
00:22:48,617 --> 00:22:50,828
What is going on today?

220
00:22:51,871 --> 00:22:53,080
I'll go check it out.

221
00:22:55,416 --> 00:22:58,252
Geez.

222
00:23:05,342 --> 00:23:06,343
Remember.

223
00:23:06,844 --> 00:23:12,348
If you want to find your wife,
come to 543-7, Shinyu-dong by 11 p.m.

224
00:23:12,349 --> 00:23:13,474
If you don't,

225
00:23:13,475 --> 00:23:15,561
you may never get to see her again.

226
00:23:18,105 --> 00:23:19,773
What the… Kang Taeju.

227
00:23:21,066 --> 00:23:23,611
Hey, answer me! Kang Taeju!

228
00:23:26,989 --> 00:23:28,741
Can't they do anything about this?

229
00:23:36,624 --> 00:23:38,917
Hey, you know
we've got lines to the annex, right?

230
00:23:38,918 --> 00:23:40,419
- Yes, sir.
- Give them a call.

231
00:23:42,504 --> 00:23:44,005
Come on, man.

232
00:23:44,006 --> 00:23:45,633
Hey, go check out the annex building!

233
00:23:46,383 --> 00:23:48,177
I'll go check it out.

234
00:23:50,220 --> 00:23:51,931
Don't bother. I'll just call them.

235
00:23:57,144 --> 00:23:58,811
- Come over here.
- I'll check it out.

236
00:23:58,812 --> 00:24:00,396
- Kang Taeju!
- Hurry up…

237
00:24:00,397 --> 00:24:01,398
Get him!

238
00:24:02,733 --> 00:24:03,984
Hey, get that punk!

239
00:24:04,652 --> 00:24:06,070
He's going up!

240
00:24:07,863 --> 00:24:09,614
Get him now!

241
00:24:09,615 --> 00:24:11,616
Get him! Move it!

242
00:24:11,617 --> 00:24:13,451
Third floor! Get to the third floor!

243
00:24:13,452 --> 00:24:14,662
Kang Taeju!

244
00:24:26,840 --> 00:24:28,675
- You two take the right side.
- Yes, sir.

245
00:24:28,676 --> 00:24:30,886
You guys take the roof.
The rest of you, with me.

246
00:24:41,522 --> 00:24:43,774
Quick! Go up!

247
00:24:58,914 --> 00:25:00,582
-  Did you see him?
- Negative.

248
00:25:19,143 --> 00:25:20,393
What about the rooftop?

249
00:25:20,394 --> 00:25:22,228
- Check out the main gate.
-  Yes, sir.

250
00:25:22,229 --> 00:25:24,356
- Come on, let's hurry!
-  We'll check it out!

251
00:26:13,489 --> 00:26:17,992
So, guys, we've worked with
a lot of different codes so far, right?

252
00:26:17,993 --> 00:26:19,786
Yeah!

253
00:26:19,787 --> 00:26:22,663
But see, you don't have to memorize
what every single code does

254
00:26:22,664 --> 00:26:24,332
or what you can do with it.

255
00:26:24,333 --> 00:26:27,711
The thing is,
even I don't have all of that memorized.

256
00:26:28,462 --> 00:26:29,921
- But Mr. Noh!
-  Yes?

257
00:26:29,922 --> 00:26:32,381
How can we use the codes
if we don't memorize them?

258
00:26:32,382 --> 00:26:33,966
Good point.

259
00:26:33,967 --> 00:26:37,512
When there's need, you can
look up the codes online to practice,

260
00:26:37,513 --> 00:26:41,015
or just let me know anytime you want.
You all have my number, right?

261
00:26:41,016 --> 00:26:42,642
Yeah!

262
00:26:42,643 --> 00:26:45,770
All right, shall we check out
what we'll be learning today?

263
00:26:45,771 --> 00:26:47,272
Okay, turn to page 20.

264
00:27:25,227 --> 00:27:26,812
Are you feeling any better?

265
00:27:49,543 --> 00:27:50,836
I don't know.

266
00:27:52,129 --> 00:27:53,462
I'm telling you.

267
00:27:53,463 --> 00:27:55,882
It's going to get a lot worse.

268
00:27:55,883 --> 00:28:00,262
It only gets scarier
and more frightening over time.

269
00:28:00,971 --> 00:28:03,432
No one could ever get used to this.

270
00:28:04,349 --> 00:28:05,851
How did he get you?

271
00:28:06,393 --> 00:28:08,436
I got jumped from behind

272
00:28:08,437 --> 00:28:10,731
while I was leaving
a fortune teller's place.

273
00:28:11,481 --> 00:28:13,775
I was sleeping at home,

274
00:28:14,818 --> 00:28:17,237
and he was standing right there
when I opened my eyes.

275
00:28:18,614 --> 00:28:20,949
But I have no idea
why he's doing this to me.

276
00:28:21,450 --> 00:28:25,746
I think I have an idea
as to why this is happening to me.

277
00:28:26,830 --> 00:28:27,831
Why's that?

278
00:28:28,415 --> 00:28:31,543
See, I did a bad thing.

279
00:28:34,504 --> 00:28:36,005
"A bad thing"?

280
00:28:36,006 --> 00:28:41,053
There's a spirit we serve in our home,
and I turned my back on them.

281
00:28:41,970 --> 00:28:44,931
Things got so rough,
and I couldn't see a way forward,

282
00:28:44,932 --> 00:28:47,768
so I sought out
other shamans out of desperation.

283
00:28:49,019 --> 00:28:51,855
So maybe, do you think

284
00:28:53,398 --> 00:28:55,609
you might have wronged someone?

285
00:28:56,401 --> 00:28:58,070
Maybe you hurt someone.

286
00:28:59,279 --> 00:29:04,618
You know, being here really opened my eyes
to what a horrible thing I'd done.

287
00:29:10,749 --> 00:29:12,167
She's not praying.

288
00:29:17,172 --> 00:29:19,423
All right, guys. Everybody done reading?

289
00:29:19,424 --> 00:29:20,467
MR. NOH'S COMPUTER CLASS

290
00:29:34,648 --> 00:29:36,942
SEONGJIN POLICE STATION

291
00:29:43,782 --> 00:29:44,783
I found him!

292
00:29:48,453 --> 00:29:49,454
Play it back.

293
00:29:55,669 --> 00:29:57,004
He jumped out of that window?

294
00:29:57,629 --> 00:29:59,923
He's lost it. Isn't he a doctor?

295
00:30:00,590 --> 00:30:01,717
Are you admiring the guy?

296
00:30:02,676 --> 00:30:03,926
Get a move on.

297
00:30:03,927 --> 00:30:04,928
Let's roll.

298
00:30:05,512 --> 00:30:06,763
Come on!

299
00:30:11,184 --> 00:30:13,145
Mom, here.

300
00:30:21,987 --> 00:30:23,154
Detective.

301
00:30:23,155 --> 00:30:25,531
What's going on? Where's Taeju?

302
00:30:25,532 --> 00:30:26,782
- He bolted.
- What?

303
00:30:26,783 --> 00:30:28,868
Wait a minute! What are you talking about?

304
00:30:28,869 --> 00:30:30,703
He ran off during the interrogation.

305
00:30:30,704 --> 00:30:32,122
- I…
- What…

306
00:30:33,373 --> 00:30:34,707
- What…
- What is going on?

307
00:30:34,708 --> 00:30:36,084
He ran away?

308
00:30:37,044 --> 00:30:41,213
You said your son is
incapable of doing anything bad.

309
00:30:41,214 --> 00:30:44,843
So why would he run
if he hasn't done anything wrong?

310
00:30:46,511 --> 00:30:49,056
I'm sure he had his reasons.

311
00:30:50,223 --> 00:30:51,932
Just give him some time.

312
00:30:51,933 --> 00:30:53,518
Reasons?

313
00:30:54,519 --> 00:30:56,855
There's no excuse
for running away from the police!

314
00:30:58,231 --> 00:30:59,274
My goodness.

315
00:30:59,983 --> 00:31:01,985
What a mother you are.

316
00:31:02,569 --> 00:31:05,071
What a loving mother!

317
00:31:05,072 --> 00:31:08,825
It's just incredible! Give me a break.

318
00:31:12,704 --> 00:31:15,457
Oh, Mom. Are you okay?

319
00:31:16,374 --> 00:31:19,210
Let's sit you down. There you go.

320
00:31:19,211 --> 00:31:22,421
- Taeyeong.
- Yeah.

321
00:31:22,422 --> 00:31:25,299
- What in the world is happening?
- Exactly.

322
00:31:25,300 --> 00:31:27,384
- Why would he… Why…
- That idiot!

323
00:31:27,385 --> 00:31:30,514
Why did he run away
in a situation like this?

324
00:31:31,765 --> 00:31:33,140
Ugh, geez.

325
00:31:33,141 --> 00:31:34,226
It's okay.

326
00:31:35,477 --> 00:31:37,646
WOORI TOGETHER MEDICAL CENTER

327
00:32:05,799 --> 00:32:07,050
Hey, excuse me.

328
00:32:07,968 --> 00:32:09,593
Oh, hey. It's just me.

329
00:32:09,594 --> 00:32:11,221
Oh, hello. Dr. Kang.

330
00:32:12,055 --> 00:32:13,473
What are you doing here so late?

331
00:32:15,475 --> 00:32:17,269
I forgot something in my office.

332
00:32:18,520 --> 00:32:20,313
- Have a good one.
- You too.

333
00:33:08,612 --> 00:33:10,322
OPERATING ROOM

334
00:33:13,575 --> 00:33:14,950
ACCESS GRANTED

335
00:33:14,951 --> 00:33:20,749
RESTRICTED AREA
AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY

336
00:34:29,901 --> 00:34:31,402
Geez, you scared me.

337
00:34:31,403 --> 00:34:34,321
- Hey, Chiung.
- What are you doing here so late?

338
00:34:34,322 --> 00:34:36,950
You know,
I just left something in the office.

339
00:34:38,076 --> 00:34:40,078
Must be pretty damn important.

340
00:34:40,745 --> 00:34:43,122
What about you? What are you doing here?

341
00:34:43,123 --> 00:34:45,124
I'm on call tonight.

342
00:34:45,125 --> 00:34:47,668
Pharmacy wanted me
to check the anesthetics inventory.

343
00:34:47,669 --> 00:34:49,379
I see.

344
00:34:50,213 --> 00:34:52,465
- Hang in there, then. See you.
- Okay.

345
00:34:54,843 --> 00:34:55,885
Chiung.

346
00:34:56,886 --> 00:34:57,970
Hmm?

347
00:34:57,971 --> 00:34:59,598
What? You got something to say?

348
00:35:01,266 --> 00:35:02,350
Well, I…

349
00:35:03,393 --> 00:35:05,728
I had a bit of an incident today.

350
00:35:05,729 --> 00:35:06,938
Oh, what happened?

351
00:35:07,564 --> 00:35:09,941
Well, it's kind of serious.

352
00:35:10,984 --> 00:35:11,985
Yeah.

353
00:35:12,944 --> 00:35:15,404
Now that you mention it,
you're a mess, man.

354
00:35:15,405 --> 00:35:17,157
What's going on?

355
00:35:19,618 --> 00:35:20,743
It's nothing.

356
00:35:20,744 --> 00:35:21,995
I'll tell you later.

357
00:35:22,621 --> 00:35:26,333
You know, actually…
Could you lend me your car?

358
00:35:27,334 --> 00:35:29,669
My car? Where's yours?

359
00:35:30,503 --> 00:35:34,174
Mine's… What's with all the questions?
You'll get it back tomorrow.

360
00:35:35,216 --> 00:35:36,634
Yeah, whatever.

361
00:35:36,635 --> 00:35:38,219
It's on level B3.

362
00:35:40,430 --> 00:35:42,098
Is it something to do with your wife?

363
00:35:43,141 --> 00:35:44,142
It is, right?

364
00:35:45,185 --> 00:35:47,729
Something's going on, right? What is it?

365
00:35:52,442 --> 00:35:53,818
It's okay. You can tell me.

366
00:35:54,944 --> 00:35:56,154
The thing is…

367
00:35:57,656 --> 00:35:58,739
Seyun got…

368
00:36:02,369 --> 00:36:03,912
Sorry, let me take this real quick.

369
00:36:06,623 --> 00:36:07,624
This is Choi.

370
00:36:10,251 --> 00:36:12,169
Hey, Dr. Choi, it's me.

371
00:36:12,170 --> 00:36:14,171
I'll cut right to the chase.

372
00:36:14,172 --> 00:36:16,423
Have you heard from Taeju at all?

373
00:36:16,424 --> 00:36:18,926
- Yeah, what a coincidence.
- What?

374
00:36:18,927 --> 00:36:20,595
Are you with him right now?

375
00:36:22,138 --> 00:36:23,640
Answer with "yes" or "no" only.

376
00:36:25,183 --> 00:36:26,267
Yes.

377
00:36:29,646 --> 00:36:32,564
Where are you right now? At the hospital?

378
00:36:32,565 --> 00:36:33,649
Yes.

379
00:36:33,650 --> 00:36:35,567
Okay, he's at the hospital.

380
00:36:35,568 --> 00:36:38,320
I'll make the call to the police then.

381
00:36:38,321 --> 00:36:40,448
Listen to me carefully, Dr. Choi.

382
00:36:41,282 --> 00:36:44,703
That bastard kidnapped my daughter!

383
00:36:54,671 --> 00:36:56,088
What are you talking about?

384
00:36:56,089 --> 00:36:57,881
He’s got her hidden somewhere.

385
00:36:57,882 --> 00:37:01,094
He just bolted from the police station
while they were interrogating him!

386
00:37:02,178 --> 00:37:05,140
To find Seyun,
we have to catch that bastard.

387
00:37:06,057 --> 00:37:08,475
The police are on their way,

388
00:37:08,476 --> 00:37:10,894
so you have to keep him there,
no matter what.

389
00:37:10,895 --> 00:37:11,896
Do you hear me?

390
00:37:14,023 --> 00:37:15,400
Yeah, I got it.

391
00:37:20,029 --> 00:37:23,866
Chiung, I'm so sorry. I'll explain later!

392
00:37:23,867 --> 00:37:25,618
Have you lost your mind?

393
00:37:29,080 --> 00:37:30,789
- Hey, who's there?
- Go, stop him.

394
00:37:30,790 --> 00:37:32,041
Dr. Choi?

395
00:37:33,042 --> 00:37:34,251
Dr. Choi!

396
00:37:34,252 --> 00:37:36,087
I said, go and stop Dr. Kang!

397
00:37:37,213 --> 00:37:38,423
Okay!

398
00:38:09,120 --> 00:38:10,454
- Hello.
- Dr. Kang.

399
00:38:10,455 --> 00:38:12,080
- What are you doing?
- Sorry.

400
00:38:12,081 --> 00:38:13,582
Just get out for a minute.

401
00:38:13,583 --> 00:38:15,709
- Right, yeah.
- We'll talk outside the car.

402
00:38:15,710 --> 00:38:18,212
- This seat belt just won't…
- Yeah, I'll do it for you.

403
00:38:18,213 --> 00:38:19,630
There we go. Come on.

404
00:38:19,631 --> 00:38:21,757
- No, listen, this is…
- It's just for a moment.

405
00:38:21,758 --> 00:38:24,593
- Look, Chief. You got it all wrong.
- I'm sure I do.

406
00:38:24,594 --> 00:38:25,677
I don't think so.

407
00:38:25,678 --> 00:38:28,055
- I understand.
- Could you… I said, you can't go.

408
00:38:28,056 --> 00:38:30,474
- I'll tell you later. I swear.
- Come on.

409
00:38:30,475 --> 00:38:31,558
I got it.

410
00:38:31,559 --> 00:38:34,979
I'll radio upstairs, so you can talk
after I hear from them. Stay right there.

411
00:38:38,233 --> 00:38:39,650
Dr. Kang!

412
00:38:39,651 --> 00:38:41,945
Stay away!

413
00:38:42,862 --> 00:38:44,238
I'm so sorry!

414
00:38:47,867 --> 00:38:49,910
Do your homework, Yuhyeon. Okay?

415
00:38:49,911 --> 00:38:51,078
- Okay, fine!
- Bye.

416
00:38:51,079 --> 00:38:53,539
- Bye.
- See you.

417
00:38:56,709 --> 00:38:57,710
Oh, hey, what's up?

418
00:39:02,215 --> 00:39:06,343
It's been blinking on and off
for the past few days,

419
00:39:06,344 --> 00:39:09,722
and now it's completely stopped working.

420
00:39:10,682 --> 00:39:14,310
I couldn't take any payments.
It's really been a nightmare.

421
00:39:15,019 --> 00:39:16,270
What do you think?

422
00:39:16,271 --> 00:39:17,938
You think you can fix it?

423
00:39:17,939 --> 00:39:20,607
See. It's all the dust
that's built up in here.

424
00:39:20,608 --> 00:39:22,067
That's why it wouldn't read.

425
00:39:22,068 --> 00:39:24,028
- It should work now.
- Ah.

426
00:39:27,115 --> 00:39:28,116
There it is.

427
00:39:29,284 --> 00:39:32,619
My goodness! Now it works, huh?

428
00:39:32,620 --> 00:39:33,912
How much do I owe you?

429
00:39:33,913 --> 00:39:35,622
Oh, don't worry about it.

430
00:39:35,623 --> 00:39:39,376
Oh, come on. I feel bad
you help me out all the time.

431
00:39:39,377 --> 00:39:42,714
What's there to feel bad about?
Plus, who else would you get help from?

432
00:39:43,840 --> 00:39:46,885
Well, thank you.
Why don't you stay for dinner then?

433
00:39:47,468 --> 00:39:50,054
- Have a seat right here, okay?
- No, it's fine.

434
00:39:50,930 --> 00:39:53,016
- Come on. Have a seat. Okay?
- You don't have to.

435
00:39:55,268 --> 00:39:56,560
Thank you so much.

436
00:39:56,561 --> 00:39:59,771
JANG SUNDAEGUK

437
00:39:59,772 --> 00:40:02,399
Sweetheart, can you set his table?

438
00:40:02,400 --> 00:40:03,567
Okay, Grandma.

439
00:40:03,568 --> 00:40:05,986
Is that your granddaughter
you always talk about?

440
00:40:05,987 --> 00:40:07,196
Yes, she is.

441
00:40:12,118 --> 00:40:15,288
Your grandmother's told me all about you.

442
00:40:15,955 --> 00:40:17,290
- Nice to meet you.
- Likewise.

443
00:40:17,874 --> 00:40:22,378
You know Woori Together Medical Center?
She works as a nurse there.

444
00:40:23,004 --> 00:40:24,713
Oh.

445
00:40:24,714 --> 00:40:26,214
Yeah, I've been there.

446
00:40:26,215 --> 00:40:30,260
She helps me out
whenever she can, after her shift.

447
00:40:30,261 --> 00:40:33,514
She's not like
the other young people these days.

448
00:40:34,474 --> 00:40:35,934
I've raised a fine girl.

449
00:40:37,936 --> 00:40:40,355
You really have. You must be proud of her.

450
00:40:40,939 --> 00:40:43,774
Just sit tight,
and I'll get your food ready.

451
00:40:43,775 --> 00:40:45,400
Thank you.

452
00:40:45,401 --> 00:40:47,611
That's 22,000 won.
Do you need your receipt?

453
00:40:47,612 --> 00:40:49,863
-  It's fine.
-  Moving on to our next story…

454
00:40:49,864 --> 00:40:50,948
-  Bye.
- Thank you.

455
00:40:50,949 --> 00:40:53,367
An armed robbery occurred
at a convenience store

456
00:40:53,368 --> 00:40:56,036
in Jungang-dong, Seongjin-gu,
around 8:40 tonight.

457
00:40:56,037 --> 00:40:59,539
Police took over 20 minutes to arrive
after receiving the report,

458
00:40:59,540 --> 00:41:01,375
allowing the suspect to escape.

459
00:41:01,376 --> 00:41:05,087
An unexplained power outage
at Seongjin Police Station

460
00:41:05,088 --> 00:41:08,049
disrupted communications,
delaying the initial response.

461
00:41:14,555 --> 00:41:17,599
I mean, he did seem a little off
when he came in,

462
00:41:17,600 --> 00:41:19,352
but I didn't think much of it.

463
00:41:19,936 --> 00:41:24,231
And then Dr. Choi told me
to stop him, so I did.

464
00:41:24,232 --> 00:41:27,860
But then, Dr. Kang took my pepper gun
and sprayed me with it.

465
00:41:28,820 --> 00:41:30,738
My eyes haven't stopped watering since.

466
00:41:31,531 --> 00:41:32,573
You all right?

467
00:41:33,533 --> 00:41:35,034
Yeah, I'm fine.

468
00:41:35,910 --> 00:41:37,077
But…

469
00:41:37,078 --> 00:41:41,082
Listen. They're missing about six vials
of anesthetics in the operating room safe.

470
00:41:41,874 --> 00:41:43,417
They're missing some scalpels

471
00:41:43,418 --> 00:41:45,670
and surgical instruments
for cutting through bones.

472
00:41:46,254 --> 00:41:47,255
Right.

473
00:41:48,131 --> 00:41:50,258
When are you going to catch this bastard?

474
00:41:51,092 --> 00:41:53,885
What if something happens to my daughter?

475
00:41:53,886 --> 00:41:55,763
Just a moment. Excuse me.

476
00:41:57,390 --> 00:41:58,391
Yes, talk.

477
00:41:58,933 --> 00:42:02,269
Yeah, Captain. It looks like
after carjacking the vehicle,

478
00:42:02,270 --> 00:42:04,855
Kang drove out of the parking garage
at 9:17 p.m.,

479
00:42:04,856 --> 00:42:07,149
and took a turn
toward Angok-ro at 9:18 p.m.

480
00:42:07,150 --> 00:42:08,692
He couldn't have gotten far then.

481
00:42:08,693 --> 00:42:12,154
Put out an APB on the vehicle
and have dispatch track him using WASS.

482
00:42:12,155 --> 00:42:14,531
Alert all nearby units for backup.

483
00:42:14,532 --> 00:42:16,701
- I'm moving out now.
- Copy that.

484
00:42:17,660 --> 00:42:19,912
It's go time. Let's roll.

485
00:42:23,833 --> 00:42:27,587
If you can't save my daughter,
I will hold you accountable.

486
00:42:28,337 --> 00:42:29,797
We'll do everything we can.

487
00:42:38,181 --> 00:42:39,348
Move it!

488
00:42:46,230 --> 00:42:48,316
- Head toward Angok-ro.
- Copy that.

489
00:43:04,165 --> 00:43:05,583
You bastard.

490
00:43:06,250 --> 00:43:07,752
You bastard.

491
00:43:08,503 --> 00:43:09,921
You bastard.

492
00:43:10,421 --> 00:43:11,547
You scumbag.

493
00:43:24,102 --> 00:43:25,603
You all right?

494
00:43:27,188 --> 00:43:29,023
He's such a bastard.

495
00:43:33,402 --> 00:43:34,403
Right.

496
00:43:36,864 --> 00:43:39,158
That's why he does these things.

497
00:43:40,535 --> 00:43:41,786
No, not him.

498
00:43:42,286 --> 00:43:43,621
I'm talking about my husband.

499
00:43:46,916 --> 00:43:47,917
What?

500
00:43:50,002 --> 00:43:53,171
The kidnapper called my husband
and told him I was kidnapped,

501
00:43:53,172 --> 00:43:56,676
but he just said, "Do whatever
you want with her" and hung up.

502
00:43:57,510 --> 00:43:59,428
He hasn't even picked up since.

503
00:44:05,643 --> 00:44:08,396
But the kidnapper
may not have been telling the truth.

504
00:44:09,230 --> 00:44:10,731
Maybe he made it all up.

505
00:44:12,483 --> 00:44:15,319
I had a fight
with my husband before I left.

506
00:44:16,028 --> 00:44:17,280
He said it to my face.

507
00:44:18,114 --> 00:44:20,740
That he was glad we didn't have children.

508
00:44:20,741 --> 00:44:23,244
That he wishes I would just die already.

509
00:44:24,954 --> 00:44:28,624
Me dying here is
exactly what he'd wish for.

510
00:44:29,876 --> 00:44:31,711
He'd be happy if I died.

511
00:44:32,879 --> 00:44:36,257
Was that your husband who was crying

512
00:44:36,966 --> 00:44:40,553
on the phone earlier?

513
00:44:49,478 --> 00:44:50,855
Yes, it was.

514
00:44:52,523 --> 00:44:55,775
You guys must have had
a good marriage going.

515
00:44:55,776 --> 00:44:58,404
We're both stuck here,
but I got to say, I'm jealous.

516
00:45:00,781 --> 00:45:01,949
What's your name?

517
00:45:03,242 --> 00:45:05,077
Mine's Lee Seonja.

518
00:45:07,830 --> 00:45:09,248
My name is Ko Seyun.

519
00:45:11,751 --> 00:45:13,460
Hey, Seyun.

520
00:45:13,461 --> 00:45:15,588
Can you do me a favor?

521
00:45:17,215 --> 00:45:18,216
What is it?

522
00:45:19,300 --> 00:45:21,552
When you get out of here,

523
00:45:22,386 --> 00:45:25,180
can you let the police know

524
00:45:25,181 --> 00:45:29,727
that Lee Seonja from Songmu-dong
died in this place?

525
00:45:31,562 --> 00:45:33,731
I don't have much time left.

526
00:45:34,398 --> 00:45:37,109
I'm going to die soon.

527
00:45:47,828 --> 00:45:49,413
PUBLIC SERVICE CENTER

528
00:45:52,416 --> 00:45:53,500
Hello?

529
00:45:53,501 --> 00:45:55,753
Taeyeong, it's me.

530
00:46:05,554 --> 00:46:06,555
You idiot.

531
00:46:07,682 --> 00:46:09,099
Where are you?

532
00:46:09,100 --> 00:46:10,309
What's going on?

533
00:46:10,893 --> 00:46:12,311
Why did you run away?

534
00:46:12,895 --> 00:46:15,730
I'll explain later.
How's Mom? Is she doing okay?

535
00:46:15,731 --> 00:46:17,274
Of course she isn't.

536
00:46:17,275 --> 00:46:19,110
She almost fainted because of you.

537
00:46:19,610 --> 00:46:21,821
Why would you run from the police?

538
00:46:22,530 --> 00:46:23,531
Hold on.

539
00:46:24,073 --> 00:46:25,157
It wasn't you, was it?

540
00:46:26,200 --> 00:46:27,243
Of course not.

541
00:46:28,828 --> 00:46:30,788
It wasn't me, but…

542
00:46:32,581 --> 00:46:34,500
She did get kidnapped because of me.

543
00:46:36,585 --> 00:46:38,545
I have to save Seyun.

544
00:46:38,546 --> 00:46:40,130
What are you talking about?

545
00:46:40,131 --> 00:46:42,340
You should be getting help
from the police.

546
00:46:42,341 --> 00:46:43,883
You can't do this on your own.

547
00:46:43,884 --> 00:46:46,262
You think you're some kind of superhero?

548
00:46:48,306 --> 00:46:49,307
Yeah.

549
00:46:50,641 --> 00:46:52,685
I kind of wish I was.

550
00:46:53,352 --> 00:46:54,395
Hey, listen.

551
00:46:55,062 --> 00:46:56,814
Talk to Mom for me, okay?

552
00:46:57,398 --> 00:46:59,399
Get back here and tell her yourself.

553
00:46:59,400 --> 00:47:02,403
If you didn't do it,
it'll all be revealed in time, right?

554
00:47:03,863 --> 00:47:05,780
Don't go making things worse, man.

555
00:47:05,781 --> 00:47:08,492
Listen to your big brother, Taeju. Okay?

556
00:47:10,911 --> 00:47:11,996
Taeju?

557
00:47:12,580 --> 00:47:13,664
Taeju.

558
00:47:16,000 --> 00:47:18,377
Taeju, where are you now?

559
00:47:18,919 --> 00:47:20,796
You're not hurt, are you?

560
00:47:21,339 --> 00:47:23,299
Hey, Mom. I'm fine.

561
00:47:25,926 --> 00:47:27,594
But I can't go back there right now.

562
00:47:27,595 --> 00:47:30,305
Seyun will be in more danger
if I stay at the station.

563
00:47:30,306 --> 00:47:32,015
What are you talking about?

564
00:47:32,016 --> 00:47:36,228
Why would you being at the station
put Seyun in danger?

565
00:47:36,771 --> 00:47:37,772
Taeju.

566
00:47:38,647 --> 00:47:40,149
Come back. It's not too late.

567
00:47:43,194 --> 00:47:44,195
Mom, just…

568
00:47:45,613 --> 00:47:49,407
Just trust me and give me some time.
I promise I'll bring Seyun home.

569
00:47:49,408 --> 00:47:51,452
Taeju.

570
00:47:55,873 --> 00:47:57,624
- Taeju…
- What is it, Mom?

571
00:47:57,625 --> 00:47:58,918
What did he say?

572
00:48:17,228 --> 00:48:19,312
RED LIGHT AND SPEEDING
SURVEILLANCE CAMERA

573
00:48:22,817 --> 00:48:25,276
Captain, we got an update
on Kang's location.

574
00:48:25,277 --> 00:48:27,320
- Where?
- He was at Deoksam Intersection

575
00:48:27,321 --> 00:48:28,947
at 9:46 p.m.

576
00:48:28,948 --> 00:48:30,282
Heading that way.

577
00:50:56,178 --> 00:50:57,429
It's working.

578
00:51:58,616 --> 00:52:01,076
- Just make it quick.
- Yeah. We'd like to, but…

579
00:52:08,334 --> 00:52:11,169
Yujeong Intersection.
Plate number 682T 1228.

580
00:52:11,170 --> 00:52:12,713
Visual on suspect vehicle.

581
00:52:15,341 --> 00:52:16,342
Hey.

582
00:52:17,009 --> 00:52:18,177
Yujeong Intersection?

583
00:52:19,011 --> 00:52:20,012
Okay, on my way.

584
00:52:20,554 --> 00:52:22,597
Let's take the long way
through Shinyu-dong.

585
00:52:22,598 --> 00:52:23,681
Copy that.

586
00:52:23,682 --> 00:52:25,976
- Send backup to Yujeong Intersection.
- Sir.

587
00:52:26,560 --> 00:52:28,728
Suspect vehicle
is on Yujeong Intersection.

588
00:52:28,729 --> 00:52:30,397
All nearby units, respond for backup.

589
00:52:53,253 --> 00:52:55,881
Plate number 1228, please pull over.

590
00:52:56,382 --> 00:52:58,133
Pull over, 1228.

591
00:52:58,717 --> 00:52:59,843
I repeat, 1228.

592
00:53:08,435 --> 00:53:11,105
I repeat. Pull over, 1228.

593
00:53:11,897 --> 00:53:14,316
I repeat, 1228. Stop the vehicle.

594
00:53:36,088 --> 00:53:38,298
Suspect vehicle is heading
toward Shinyu-dong.

595
00:53:40,134 --> 00:53:42,136
Units two and three, in pursuit.

596
00:53:57,025 --> 00:53:58,152
Kang Taeju!

597
00:53:59,153 --> 00:54:00,570
Pull over right now!

598
00:54:00,571 --> 00:54:02,531
Stop the car, you bastard!
This is dangerous!

599
00:54:03,866 --> 00:54:05,033
Kang Taeju!

600
00:54:05,909 --> 00:54:07,202
Stop being so reckless!

601
00:54:09,955 --> 00:54:11,165
Pull over!

602
00:54:13,584 --> 00:54:14,667
Kang Taeju!

603
00:54:14,668 --> 00:54:16,336
Get in front of him.

604
00:54:17,004 --> 00:54:18,797
Cut him off! Get in front of him!

605
00:54:26,430 --> 00:54:28,056
Darn it.

606
00:54:49,578 --> 00:54:50,953
Turn around! Step on it!

607
00:54:50,954 --> 00:54:53,706
Control, we lost
the suspect vehicle during pursuit.

608
00:54:53,707 --> 00:54:55,125
Plate number 1228.

609
00:55:59,231 --> 00:56:00,565
Kang Taeju!

610
00:56:00,566 --> 00:56:03,150
Stop the car! Stop!

611
00:56:03,151 --> 00:56:04,986
You bastard!

612
00:56:04,987 --> 00:56:07,239
Hey! Kang Taeju!

613
00:58:50,235 --> 00:58:55,156
THE HUSBAND

614
00:59:35,197 --> 00:59:36,572
Put out an APB on Kang Taeju.

615
00:59:36,573 --> 00:59:39,116
A standoff erupted
between police and a neurosurgeon

616
00:59:39,117 --> 00:59:43,412
suspected of orchestrating
his wife's kidnapping and murder.

617
00:59:43,413 --> 00:59:45,915
What the hell? Where is my wife?

618
00:59:45,916 --> 00:59:48,542
- Answer me!
- It's up to you to figure it out now.

619
00:59:48,543 --> 00:59:50,045
Are you working with that bastard?

620
00:59:51,421 --> 00:59:56,884
I know exactly what you're
thinking and doing, wherever you are.

621
00:59:56,885 --> 00:59:58,677
Have you ever killed a person before?

622
00:59:58,678 --> 01:00:01,180
For his wife…

623
01:00:01,181 --> 01:00:02,848
Could Kang Taeju kill a person?

624
01:00:02,849 --> 01:00:04,308
Are you out of your mind?

625
01:00:04,309 --> 01:00:07,187
The three billion you have here.
I need you to hand it over to me.

626
01:00:08,188 --> 01:00:10,190
Translated by Hyun Sik Yoon
